---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Moose Sports Empire"
  description="Privacy policy for the Moose Sports Empire fantasy baseball app."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text) mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text) mb-3">
          1. Overview
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
          Moose Sports Empire is a self-hosted, private fantasy baseball
          companion application for Yahoo H2H Categories leagues. This
          application is not affiliated with Yahoo Inc. or Major League
          Baseball.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text) mb-3">
          2. Data We Collect
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed list-disc pl-5">
          <li>
            <strong class="text-(--color-text)">Yahoo Account Data:</strong> When
            you log in with Yahoo, we receive your Yahoo GUID, display name, email,
            and fantasy league data via the Yahoo Fantasy Sports API (read-only scope).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-(--color-text)">Session Data:</strong> We store session
            actions in a server-side log for auditing purposes. Logs are purged after
            30 days. No IP addresses are stored.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-(--color-text)">League Data:</strong> Team names,
            standings, matchup results, and player statistics are fetched from Yahoo
            and stored locally for performance.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text) mb-3">
          3. Data We Do Not Collect
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Email addresses</li>
          <li>IP addresses</li>
          <li>Payment information</li>
          <li>
            Any data from Yahoo beyond what is required for league
            administration
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text) mb-3">
          4. AI-Generated Content
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
          Weekly recaps are generated using Google Gemini (via Google AI Studio)
          or OpenRouter as a fallback. League and player statistics are sent to
          these services for recap generation. No personally identifiable
          information beyond public fantasy league data is included in AI
          prompts. Raw prompt data is purged after 30 days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text) mb-3">
          5. Token Security
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
          Yahoo OAuth tokens are encrypted using Fernet symmetric encryption
          before storage. Tokens are never stored in plaintext. Sessions are
          managed via HTTP-only, secure, SameSite cookies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text) mb-3">
          6. Data Retention
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Session logs: 30 days</li>
          <li>AI usage logs: 30 days</li>
          <li>Recap stat payloads: 30 days</li>
          <li>League/player data: retained for the season duration</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text) mb-3">
          7. Self-Hosted Instance
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
          This application is self-hosted by your league commissioner. The
          commissioner controls all data stored on this instance. If you have
          questions about your data, contact your league commissioner directly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-(--color-text) mb-3">
          8. Open Source
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-(--color-text-muted) leading-relaxed">
          This application is open source under the MIT license. You can review
          the full source code to understand exactly what data is collected and
          how it is used.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-(--color-border-subtle)">
      <p class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] text-(--color-text-muted)">
        Last updated: March 2026. Not affiliated with Yahoo Inc. or Major League
        Baseball.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
